	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories East London - A 2-year-old boy has drowned after he apparently wandered off, following dogs to a river, Eastern Cape police said. Captain Jackson Manatha said on Sunday the mother was busy cleaning her house in Mpahleni Village, Ngqamakhwe on Saturday when the boy disappeared. "[She] asked from other boys the whereabouts of her son," said Manatha. She was told the boy had followed the dogs to a local river. When she arrived at the water, she found her son already dead. An inquest was opened. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  